Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. Key Developments

Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 4 17
Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net premiums written of $145,229,000 compared to $197,156,000 a year ago. Net premiums earned were $138,009,000 compared to $136,802,000 a year ago. Total revenues were $266,519,000 compared to $96,692,000 a year ago. Income before income tax expense was $110,658,000 compared to loss of $53,327,000 a year ago. Net income was $104,186,000 or $0.98 per diluted share compared to loss of $51,129,000 or $0.49 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Diluted book value per share as at March 31, 2017 was $14.04. Return on beginning shareholders' equity was at 7.4% compared to negative return on beginning shareholders' equity of 3.7% a year ago. The first quarter performance, which resulted in a return on beginning shareholders' equity was primarily driven by strong investment returns of 5.8% in the period.


