					Full Description



Third Point Reinsurance Ltd., incorporated on October 6, 2011, is a holding company. Through the Company's reinsurance subsidiaries, it provides property and casualty reinsurance coverage to insurance and reinsurance companies. The Company's segments include Property and Casualty Reinsurance, and Corporate. The Company's investable assets are managed by its investment manager, Third Point LLC. The Company also writes reinsurance contracts that provide protection against adverse development on loss reserves. Through Third Point LLC, the Company makes investments globally in all sectors, and in equity, credit, commodity, currency, options and other instruments. The Company also acts as the underwriter for the majority of the premium that it underwrites.Property and Casualty ReinsuranceThe Company writes reinsurance contracts covering product lines, such as property, workers' compensation, auto, general liability, professional liability, credit and financial lines, and multi-line. The Company's property line of business primarily consists of homeowners' insurance coverage. The Company also provides quota share reinsurance. The Company's workers' compensation insurance provides wage replacement and medical benefits to employees injured in the course of employment in exchange for the mandatory relinquishment of the employee's right to sue the employer for negligence. The Company provides personal automobile insurance, which is purchased for individually owned or leased cars designed to provide the insured with financial protection against bodily injury or physical damage resulting from traffic accidents and against liability that could arise from such occurrences.The Company focuses on providing proportional reinsurance to small, single state and regional carriers. The Company's general liability insurance policies are issued to business organizations to protect them against liability claims for bodily injury and property damage arising out of premises, operations, products, and completed operations, and advertising and personal injury liability. The Company's professional liability is a form of liability insurance that helps protect professional advisors and service-providing individuals and companies from bearing the full cost of defending against a negligence claim made by a client and damages awarded in a civil lawsuit. The Company's credit and financial lines primarily consist of mortgage insurance policies. It focuses on private mortgage insurance (PMI). In addition to mortgage insurance, policies classified as credit and financial lines include political risk, trade credit, surety, financial guarantee, residual value insurance and title insurance. The Company provides multi-line reinsurance, which is reinsurance of an underlying portfolio of various different types of insurance risks. Extended warranty insurance is included in multi-line business. Extended warranty insurance compensates individuals or businesses for correction or repair necessary as a result of mechanical or electrical breakdown. The Company's extended warranty insurance business it writes excludes manufacturer defect and product recall. Extended warranty insurance covers a range of units, such as motor vehicles, vans, trucks, construction equipment and agricultural equipment. The Company also offers professional liability insurance.The Company competes with Alleghany Corporation, Arch Capital Group Ltd., AXIS Capital Holdings Ltd., Chubb Limited, Endurance Specialty Holdings Ltd., Everest Re Group, Ltd., Greenlight Reinsurance Ltd., Hamilton Insurance Group Ltd., Hannover Ruckversicherung AG, Maiden Holdings Ltd., Munchener Ruckversicherungs-Gesellschaft AG., PartnerRe Ltd., Swiss Re Limited, Tokio Marine Holdings, Inc., Watford Re Ltd. and XL Group Ltd.

