TPRE - Market Data & News
TPRE - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. (TPRE) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 25, as the stock 
gained 2.46% to close at $14.60. On the day, Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. saw 950,149 shares trade hands on 2,947 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 620,612 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $14.55 and $11.05 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $13.47, and its 200-day SMA $12.33. Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. 
has a P/B ratio of 1.04. It also has a P/E ratio of 8.2.  


Third Point Reinsurance Ltd provides property and casualty reinsurance coverage to insurance and reinsurance companies in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia.

Headquartered in Pembroke, , Third Point Reinsurance Ltd. has 26 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Robert Bredahl.


